#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:19
msgid "Background"
msgstr "Fundo"

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:21
msgid ""
"**digiKam** is an advanced digital photo management application for Linux, "
"macOS and Windows desktop. It provides a simple interface which makes "
"importing and organizing digital photographs a *snap*. digiKam enables you "
"to manage large numbers of digital photographs in Albums and to organize "
"these photographs for easy retrieval using tags (keywords), captions, "
"collections, dates, geolocation and searches. It has many features for "
"viewing, organizing, processing and sharing your images. Thus, digiKam is a "
"formidable :ref:`Digital Asset Management <asset_management>` (DAM) software "
"including powerful image editing functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:23
msgid ""
"An easy-to-use camera interface is provided as **Import Tool**, that will "
"connect to your digital camera and download photographs directly into "
"digiKam Albums. `More than 1000 digital cameras <http://www.gphoto.org/proj/"
"libgphoto2/support.php>`_ are supported by the Gphoto library. Of course, "
"any media or card reader supported by your operating system will interface "
"with digiKam."
msgstr "Está disponível uma interface simples de usar para as câmaras como **Ferramenta de Importação**, a qual se irá ligar à sua câmara digital e irá tentar tramsferir directamemnte as fotografias para álbuns do  digiKam. `Mais de 1000 câmaras digitais <http://www.gphoto.org/proj/libgphoto2/support.php>`_ são suportadas pela biblbioteca do Gphoto. Obviamente, qualquer leitor de cartões ou outros dispositivos suportados pelo seu sistema operativo irão interagir com o digiKam."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:25
msgid ""
"digiKam incorporates a fast **Image Editor** with many image editing tools. "
"You can use the Image Editor to view your photographs, comment and rate "
"them, correct, enhance and alter them. The images post processing can be "
"easily done by a set of tools though the **Batch Queue Manager**, or by many "
"import and export tools dedicated to work with remote web services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:27
msgid ""
"To compare visually images side by side, one other tool named **Light "
"Table** is provided to select the best shots taken from a series."
msgstr "Para comparar visualmente as imagens lado-a-lado, a outra ferramenta chamada **Mesa de Luz** está disponível para seleccionar as melhores fotografias dentro de uma série."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:33
msgid "The digiKam Architecture"
msgstr "A Arquitectura do digiKam"

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:35
msgid ""
"While digiKam remains easy to use, it provides professional level features "
"by the dozens. It is fully 16 bit enabled including all available tools, "
"supports RAW format conversion through libraw, DNG export and ICC color "
"management :ref:`work flow <rawprocessing_workflow>`."
msgstr "Embora o digiKam continue fácil de usar, oferece funcionalidades a nível profissional às dúzias. Tem o suporte completo para 16 bits, incluindo todas as ferramentas disponíveis, suporta a conversão do formato RAW através da Libraw, a exportação para DNG e a gestão de cores ICC; veja o :ref:`procedimento <rawprocessing_workflow>`."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:38
msgid "Reporting Bugs"
msgstr "Comunicar Erros"

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:40
msgid ""
"digiKam is an Open Source project. This means that it relies on its users to "
"play their part by, at least, reporting problems and suggesting possible "
"improvements."
msgstr "O digiKam é um projecto em código aberto. Isto signfica que se baseia nos seus utilizadores para cumprirem a sua parte, pelo menos na parte de comunicar problemas e sugerior possíveis melhorias."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"digiKam makes it as easy as possible for you to report bugs or suggest "
"improvements. Wherever you are in the application the **Help** menu will "
"include a **Report Bugs** option. This will display a message box with a "
"highlighted link. Click on the link and your web browser will open the page "
"for the reporting system. All the information required will already be "
"filled in, just follow the instructions for completing your report."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:45
msgid "Support"
msgstr "Suporte"

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:47
msgid ""
"digiKam is a community supported project, which means that users and "
"developers support one another. If you become a regular user of digiKam you "
"are encouraged to join the digiKam Users Mailing List. You can start off by "
"asking questions to other digiKam users and hopefully soon you will be "
"answering the support questions of others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:49
msgid ""
"See the `digiKam Users Mailing List joining instructions <https://mail.kde."
"org/mailman/listinfo/digikam-users>`_ for details."
msgstr "Veja as `instruções de registo na Lista de Correio dos Utilizadores do digiKam <https://mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/digikam-users>`_ for details."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:51
msgid ""
"You can also visit the `digiKam Home Page <https://www.digikam.org/>`_ for "
"news of new releases and other digiKam related information."
msgstr "Também poderá visitar a `página Web do digiKam <https://www.digikam.org/>`_ para obter notícias de novas versões e outras informações relacionadas com o digiKam."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:54
msgid "Getting Involved"
msgstr "Como Envolver-se"

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:56
msgid ""
"There are many ways that you can get involved with the continued development "
"of digiKam. You do not need to be a software developer. You can help with "
"documentation, translation and user interface design or just contribute "
"really good ideas to the wish-list. You can also get involved by testing "
"early development code as it is being developed and providing feedback to "
"the developers. Of course, if you are a software developer then you can help "
"to make digiKam the best digital photograph application there is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:58
msgid ""
"The best way to start getting involved with digiKam is to join the "
"Developers Mailing List."
msgstr "A melhro forma de começar a envolver-se com o digiKam é associar-se à Lista de Correio de Desenvolvimento."

#: ../../getting_started/introduction.rst:60
msgid ""
"See the `digiKam Developer Mailing List joining instructions <https://mail."
"kde.org/mailman/listinfo/digikam-devel>`_ for details."
msgstr "Veja as `instruções de inscrição na Lista de Correio de Desenvolvimento do digiKam <https://mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/digikam-devel>`_ para saber mais detalhes."
